---

<Base
  title="Scar Revision in Houston, TX | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Scar Revision in Houston, TX at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Scar Revision in Houston, TX"
  headerImage="/img/tummy-tuck-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/scar-revision-houston-tx"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                Scar revision dramatically improves the appearance and decreases noticeability of your scars through surgical or non-surgical techniques. Because scar revision encompasses many techniques and procedures, it can be performed for nearly all types of scars anywhere on the body.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What non-surgical scar revision techniques do you use at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston?</h3>
                                <p>Our wide variety of non-surgical scar revision techniques here at TOPS Houston includes dermabrasion, injections, Laser scar revision, topical creams, and more. If you’re seeking revision for acne scarring and discoloration, your doctor may even recommend non-surgical MedSpa treatments like <a href="/chemical-peel-houston">chemical peels</a>, microneedling, or dermabrasion as a first option.</p>
                                <p>Non-surgical scar revision techniques are often most appropriate for facial scars, acne scars, some keloid scars, or other relatively minor scars. However, even patients with major scarring can sometimes benefit from non-surgical methods. Your doctor will help you determine what scar-revision techniques you need.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What surgical scar revision techniques do you offer at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    The surgical technique that’s best for you will depend on the type and extent of your scarring. Most scar revision surgeries are minor and can even be performed under local anesthesia. Exact techniques vary, but they typically involve carefully removing the scar with as little new trauma to the area as possible. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    For major scars that cover larger areas of the body, especially scars from burns or serious injuries, scar revision surgery can sometimes be more extensive. Depending on the severity of your scars, your surgeon may recommend skin grafting. In addition to improving the appearance of your scar, your plastic surgeon will also work to ensure that your surgery improves any pain, discomfort, or decreased mobility caused by your scars.
                                </p>

                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What about C-section scar revision?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Many Houston moms come to us seeking C-section scar revision. It’s one of our most common scar revision procedures, and we are experts in reducing your C-section surgical scars with as little downtime as possible. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Not only are we well-versed in diminishing the appearance of your C-section scars, we also offer full <a href="/mommy-makeover-houston">Mommy Makeovers</a>, including tummy tucks, to help moms feel comfortable and confident in their bodies again. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect at your initial consultation at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    At your consultation in our Houston office, you and your plastic surgeon will discuss your medical history as well as your desires for your scar revision. Your surgeon will examine your scars, decide if they are best treated through surgical or non-surgical scar revision techniques, and recommend the procedure that’s best for you. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    You’ll discuss the details of your procedure as well as your anesthesia and sedation options. You’ll have the chance to ask any and all of your questions, and you’ll be given a packet of materials specific to your scar revision procedure. At TOPS Houston, we want you to leave feeling calm, confident, and well-informed about your procedure.
                                </p>
                                <p>To take your first steps toward feeling like yourself again, <a href="/contact-us">schedule your initial consultation</a> with us today.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
